Topic 
Week 3: Grammar of Graphics and Creating Reports

Learning Objectives: 
- Translate an image of description of a graphic to a specification of the graphic using the layered grammar of graphics in ggplot2.
- Deconstruct a graphic into the data displayed and how it is mapped to visual properties.


Vitual "Worksheets" In this file include: 
1) Introduction to ggplot2: Points
2) Data Viz: Recreating Shot Plot (credit to Charlotte Wickham for original work)

Solutions can be found at: 
1) https://rpubs.com/hsmalley/dv_points
2) https://rpubs.com/hsmalley/laShot
